<TR BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=3><TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="LEFT">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl?day=21&show_all=1"><font size=2>&lt;&lt;&lt;&nbsp;DEC&nbsp;21</font></a></TD><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="CENTER"><a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl"><font size=2>HOME</font></a></TD><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><a class="addthis_button" href="http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&amp;pub=xa-4b157e7f1b908808"><img src="http://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/v2/lg-share-en.gif" width="125" height="16" alt="Bookmark and Share" style="border:0"/></a><script type="text/javascript" src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=xa-4b157e7f1b908808"></script></TD><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="RIGHT"><a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl?day=23&show_all=1"><font size=2>DEC&nbsp;23&nbsp;&gt;&gt;&gt;</font></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR>
<TR HEIGHT=5><TD COLSPAN=3 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD></TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH=5 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD>
<TD BACKGROUND="/black6.png">
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5><TR><TD>
	<TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=130 HEIGHT=130 SRC="chocs/choc_day_22.png" ALT="chocolate"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=190 SRC="globes/advent_globe_22.png" ALT="snowglobe"><table cellpadding=10 align="center" background="/black4.png" width=430><TR><TD><center><font size=6 color="#ffff00"><b><i>TRADITIONS</i></b></font><br><font size=3 color="red"><b><i>3 days to Christmas</i></b></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><p>
Christmas Eve arrives, and you do the last of your Christmas
preparations. It's now just before bedtime, you have some time to
kill, so what do you do?
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I used to have a ritual which I'd do every Christmas Eve. First, I'd
flick through the Christmas issues of the Speccy magazines as they'd
usually have plenty of festive content. The Xmas '87 issue of Your
Sinclair was perfect for a bit of festive fun with its board game,
cracker jokes competition, and stocking filler guide. Also the Xmas
<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 ALIGN="right"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH=222 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" BGCOLOR="#000000" BACKGROUND=""><TR><TD><center><object width="212" height="172"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/9L0PhqyiJgQ&hl=en_GB&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/9L0PhqyiJgQ&hl=en_GB&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="212" height="172"></embed></object><br>
<FONT size=-1 COLOR="#FFFF00"><b><u>Buggy Boy North Track</u></b></font></center><font size=-1 color="#ffffff">Nice and wintry, and those trees used to make me think of Christmas. <b><i>(6:26)</i></b></font><center><font size=-2 color="#ffffff"><i>Watch full-sized <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9L0PhqyiJgQ" target="9L0PhqyiJgQ">at YouTube</a></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><br></TD></TR></TABLE>

'88 issues of YS and Crash were utterly fabulous, both being the
largest issues those titles would ever publish. The shower of
fantastic games being released at the time helped matters immensely,
especially during the classic Christmas run-up of '88.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Soon I'd fire up my Speccy. There aren't that many decent games with a
Christmassy theme, but I'd also play three titles. First would be
<i>Buggy Boy</i>, which really isn't as perverse as it sounds. The snow
covered North track is nicely hilly and filled with pine trees to
avoid making it a fast fun game to play all the way through, and all
that snow puts me in the festive mood quite well.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 ALIGN="left"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH=222 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" BGCOLOR="#000000" BACKGROUND=""><TR><TD><center><object width="212" height="172"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/kA590l1efKI&hl=en_GB&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/kA590l1efKI&hl=en_GB&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="212" height="172"></embed></object><br>
<FONT size=-1 COLOR="#FFFF00"><b><u>Moley Christmas</u></b></font></center><font size=-1 color="#ffffff">A sweet Christmas card to get from Monty Mole. <b><i>(4:29)</i></b></font><center><font size=-2 color="#ffffff"><i>Watch full-sized <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kA590l1efKI" target="kA590l1efKI">at YouTube</a></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><br></TD></TR></TABLE>
Next up is <i>Moley Christmas</i>, which was given away with the Xmas '87
issue of YS. This is a game which is Christmassy-by-proxy. There's
nothing really about the season in the game itself apart from in the
plot, but tied with the magazine it appeared on and the Chistmassy
sequence at the end of the game, plus the fact it only takes about
three minutes to complete, makes it a firm fixture in my Christmas Eve
ritual.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<TABLE ALIGN="right" WIDTH=256 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><a href="pngs/d22_crisisatchristmas.png" target="crisisatchristmas.png"><IMG SRC="pngs/d22_crisisatchristmas_small.jpg" WIDTH=256 HEIGHT=192></a></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=1 ALIGN="CENTER"><font size=-1 color="yellow"><b><i>A lovely twee loading screen sets the scene quite nicely.</i></b></font></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
Finally there's the text adventure <i>White Door - Crisis At Christmas</i>.
Unbeknownst to me, this actually first appeared as a massive type-in
in an old issue of Sinclair User, but it was when I bought Tartan's
<i>Six-In-One</i> adventure compilation for beginners that I first played it
and fell in love with. The plot's simple - it's Christmas Eve, and
your husband or wife (you can choose which one to play) has been held
up by their car breaking down, leaving you to sort out the Christmas
presents for your two children, providing you can find out where the
presents were hidden and what you can use to wrap them with. Oh, and
your kids were also promised that Father Christmas would deliver them
personally, so you have to figure out how to dress a bit like him,
too. It's a comfortably-sized adventure for beginners, and has a nice
atmosphere throughout it - well worth checking out.
<TABLE ALIGN="center" WIDTH=400 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><a href="pngs/d22_cax1.jpg" target="cax1.jpg"><IMG SRC="pngs/d22_cax1_small.jpg" WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=100></a></TD><TD>&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD><TD><a href="pngs/d22_cax2.jpg" target="cax2.jpg"><IMG SRC="pngs/d22_cax2_small.jpg" WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=100></a></TD><TD>&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD><TD><a href="pngs/d22_cax3.jpg" target="cax3.jpg"><IMG SRC="pngs/d22_cax3_small.jpg" WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=100></a></TD><TD>&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD><TD><a href="pngs/d22_cax4.jpg" target="cax4.jpg"><IMG SRC="pngs/d22_cax4_small.jpg" WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=100></a></TD><TD>&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD><TD><a href="pngs/d22_cax5.jpg" target="cax5.jpg"><IMG SRC="pngs/d22_cax5_small.jpg" WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=100></a></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=9 ALIGN="CENTER"><font size=-1 color="yellow"><b><i>There are two ways of playing <i>Crisis At Christmas</i> - you can either download the game, or type in the game yourself. I'm actually quite relieved that I'm not one of those people who typed in the game before accidentally buying it as part of a compilation!</i></b></font></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 ALIGN="left"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH=222 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" BGCOLOR="#000000" BACKGROUND=""><TR><TD><center><object width="212" height="172"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/JAIOzM7SsMo&hl=en_GB&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/JAIOzM7SsMo&hl=en_GB&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="212" height="172"></embed></object><br>
<FONT size=-1 COLOR="#FFFF00"><b><u>Stutter Rap / Morris Minor and the Majors</u></b></font></center><font size=-1 color="#ffffff">What's Christmas without a novelty record? And don't miss <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wbDAruSSdGg" target="wbDAruSSdGg">"Stutter Rap - Unplugged"</a> for the full Stutter Experience! Also <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N8ju4h2GLD0" target="N8ju4h2GLD0">live with an 80s beat!</a> <b><i>(3:39)</i></b></font><center><font size=-2 color="#ffffff"><i>Watch full-sized <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JAIOzM7SsMo" target="JAIOzM7SsMo">at YouTube</a></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><br></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 ALIGN="right"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH=222 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" BGCOLOR="#000000" BACKGROUND=""><TR><TD><center><object width="212" height="172"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/B6lQunIGWFs&hl=en_GB&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/B6lQunIGWFs&hl=en_GB&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="212" height="172"></embed></object><br>
<FONT size=-1 COLOR="#FFFF00"><b><u>Back To The Future BBC1 Promo (1988)</u></b></font></center><font size=-1 color="#ffffff">I really looked forward to that! As there was no local cinema, TV film premieres were <i>huge</i>. <b><i>(2:31)</i></b></font><center><font size=-2 color="#ffffff"><i>Watch full-sized <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B6lQunIGWFs" target="B6lQunIGWFs">at YouTube</a></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><br></TD></TR></TABLE>
A perfect way to round off the Christmas run-up, especially with
something strong to drink and rich to eat. I'm pretty fond of brandy,
chocolate log and liqueur chocolates. Then it's a quick peek at the
telly to see if there's a good Christmas movie on before going to bed.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nowadays I don't have much time to go through all that each Christmas
Eve, but I still find five or ten minutes to fire up an emulator to
play <i>Moley Christmas</i> and <i>Crisis At Christmas</i>. After all, what would
Christmas be like without tradition?
</TD></TR></TABLE><p>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</TD><TD WIDTH=5 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD></TR>
